  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Virginia has recorded $64.2B in federal contract obligations in FY2026 to date. Award activity includes 266,642 awards with an average award size of $241K, and obligations are down 46.8% year over year. Spending so far is concentrated in a handful of buyers: the Department of Defense at $25.1B and the Department of Veterans Affairs at $17.1B together account for the largest shares of obligations. Health-related spending and IT services dominate industry receipts, with Direct Health and Medical Insurance Carriers at $14.4B and Computer Systems Design Services at $7.3B. The largest contractors in the state include TRIWEST HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE CORP at $7.7B and OPTUM PUBLIC SECTOR SOLUTIONS, INC. at $6.6B. Historical context shows FY21 obligations of $77.9B rising through FY25 to $121B before the current FY26 to date total of $64.2B. The FY2026 to date totals are partial (fiscal year to date), and all figures reported are contract obligations.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "What does the FY2026 to date total tell us about current federal buying in Virginia?",
        "body": "The FY2026 to date total of $64.2B shows current-year obligations through the fiscal year to date and is a partial total. Large buyers are driving the total: the Department of Defense at $25.1B and the Department of Veterans Affairs at $17.1B. Industry concentration is notable, with Direct Health and Medical Insurance Carriers receiving $14.4B and Computer Systems Design Services receiving $7.3B. The top vendors include TRIWEST HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE CORP at $7.7B and OPTUM PUBLIC SECTOR SOLUTIONS, INC. at $6.6B."
      },
      {
        "heading": "How does FY2026 to date compare with recent fiscal years?",
        "body": "FY2026 to date obligations of $64.2B compare with prior fiscal-year totals of $77.9B in FY21, $89.4B in FY22, $106B in FY23, $110B in FY24, and $121B in FY25. Obligations are down 46.8% year over year. The FY2026 to date figure is a partial fiscal-year total and should be interpreted as year-to-date contract obligations rather than a full-year result."
      }
    ]
  },
  "faq": [
    {
      "q": "How much federal contract money goes to Virginia?",
      "a": "Virginia has received $64.2B in federal contract obligations in FY2026 to date. That total comes from 266,642 awards with an average award size of $241K, and obligations are down 46.8% year over year. Historical annual totals were $77.9B in FY21, $89.4B in FY22, $106B in FY23, $110B in FY24, and $121B in FY25."
    },
    {
      "q": "Which agencies award the most contracts in Virginia?",
      "a": "The Department of Defense and the Department of Veterans Affairs award the most contracts in Virginia. The Department of Defense accounts for $25.1B in obligations and the Department of Veterans Affairs accounts for $17.1B; other large buyers include the Department of Homeland Security at $5.1B and the General Services Administration at $4.3B."
    },
